# Session [25] – Network+

## Main Topics
- NAT chist?  
- Tarze kar NAT  
- Estefadeh-ha dar network  

## Flashback – NAT Basics
- NAT = Network Address Translation  
- IP address haye private ro be public tabdil mikonad baraye internet access  
- Routers ya firewalls NAT ra anjam midahand  
- Nat AKA ------> Network address translation
## Explanation

### Tarze Kar
- Device dar LAN IP private dare (mesl 192.168.1.10)  
- Packet be NAT router miresad → IP private be IP public tabdil mishavad  
- Internet → reply be public IP → NAT router tabdil mikonad be private IP  

### Types of NAT
- **Static NAT** → yek private IP be yek public IP map mishavad  
- **Dynamic NAT** → private IP be yek public IP az pool allocate mishavad  
- **PAT (Port Address Translation)** → chand private IP ba yek public IP + port mapping  

### Example Table
| Private IP    | Public IP    | Type |
|---------------|-------------|------|
| 192.168.1.10  | 203.0.113.5 | Static |
| 192.168.1.11  | 203.0.113.6 | Dynamic |
| 192.168.1.0/24 | 203.0.113.10 | PAT (Port mapping) |

### Estefadeh-ha
- Access internet baraye LAN private  
- Conserving public IPs  
- Security layer (hide private network)  

